Deleting a Repo on Github:

Go to your account on Github and to the repository you want to delete.
Go to the settings tab in your repository.
Scroll all the way to the bottom of the page until you see the Danger Zone section. 
Here, click Delete this repository (Shown in RED).
You'll now see a pop up asking if you're sure you want to delete the repository. 
Enter the name of the repository in the text box
Click the I understand the consequences, delete this repository button.


Creating a repository on Github:

Make a Github account and login.
Click on the '+' sign on the navigation bar and from the dropdown select new repository.
After clicking new repository option, you will have to initialize some things like, naming your project, choosing the visibility etc. 
After performing these steps click Create Repository button.

